b'it\xe2\x80\x99s been an incredibly journey so far, and way beyond my wildest dreams. And it all started with an album recorded in Windlesham. Happy birthday +, and thank you to everyone keeping it alive,'

b'I never thought my career would go past that to be honest, and if I got that, I\xe2\x80\x99d be chuffed. When + came out, it went gold in the first week and I played to a sold our Shepherd\xe2\x80\x99s Bush 3 weeks later. Ever since then everything that has come my way has been an added bonus,'

b'I\xe2\x80\x99ve been making music for a very long time but I guess your major label debut counts as the start in the industry, so I\xe2\x80\x99m officially a decade in as of now. All I ever wanted was to have a gold album and to sell our Shepherd\xe2\x80\x99s Bush empire,'

b'I first moved up in 2008 and on my first night got inspired to write my song The City, which was the first song written and recorded for my debut album + (or Plus if you use google). It\xe2\x80\x99s been 10 years since the release of +, today is the day it came out.'

b'This is me 2011 in the Worlds End pub up in Finsbury Park, just after signing my publishing deal. I lived all over London back then, wherever anyone would have me, but Finsbury is where I\xe2\x80\x99d spend most of my evenings coz of the open mic nights there run by my mates. https://t.co/HaVdXm4Gnh'
